{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01Scb2yDQZ7QJRf85YhfUCzG","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect. I've read the entire db.ts file. Here's a comprehensive summary of what I found:\n\n## Existing Referral System Structure\n\n### Types (Lines 127-143)\n\n**ReferralCode** interface:\n- `id: number` — auto-increment PK\n- `wallet: string` — the code owner\n- `code: string` — the referral code string\n- `created_at: Date`\n- `updated_at: Date`\n\n**ReferralLink** interface:\n- `id: number` — auto-increment PK\n- `referrer_wallet: string` — who referred\n- `referee_wallet: string` — who was referred\n- `created_at: Date`\n\n### DB Methods (Lines 279-305 in Db interface; 657-716 in implementation)\n\n**Codes (insertReferralCode, getReferralCodeByWallet, getReferralCodeByCode, upsertReferralCode)**:\n- Insert throws on duplicate wallet or code\n- Get by wallet or by code string\n- Upsert uses `ON CONFLICT (wallet) DO UPDATE` to replace a wallet's code\n\n**Links (insertReferralLink, getReferralLinkByReferee, getReferralLinksByReferrer)**:\n- Insert throws on duplicate referee\n- Get single link for a referee (1-to-1 lookup)\n- Get all links where wallet is the referrer (1-to-many, ordered newest first)\n\n### Key Patterns I See\n\n1. **SQL tagged template** with postgres library:\n   ```typescript\n   const rows = await sql<Type[]>`SQL QUERY ${param}`;\n   ```\n\n2. **Normalization functions** convert numeric types:\n   - `normalizeRound()`, `normalizeTransaction()`, `normalizeCloseCallRound()` convert BigInt/string fields to numbers\n\n3. **Pagination pattern** (lines 615-650):\n   - Uses `cursor` (string ID) + `limit` (default 20, max 50)\n   - `WHERE ... AND id < ${cursor} ORDER BY id DESC LIMIT ${limit}`\n\n4. **Batch inserts** (lines 599-612):\n   - `.map()` to transform param array to object array\n   - Pass to sql with column names: `sql(values, \"col1\", \"col2\", ...)`\n\n5. **Idempotency** (lines 584-596):\n   - Single inserts use `ON CONFLICT DO NOTHING`\n   - Batch inserts also use `ON CONFLICT DO NOTHING`\n\n6. **Optional field handling**:\n   - COALESCE for updates that preserve existing values: `COALESCE(${newValue ?? null}, existing_column)`\n   - Use `sql.json()` for JSONB fields\n\n---\n\n## What's Missing for a Full Referral System\n\nThe current system only tracks:\n- Who has a referral code\n- Who referred whom (binary relationship)\n\n**No earnings/claims tracking**. There are no:\n- `ReferralEarning` or `ReferralClaim` types\n- Methods like `insertReferralEarning()`, `getReferralEarnings()`, `claimReferralBonus()`\n- Columns tracking: earned amounts, claimed amounts, claim timestamps, or claim status\n\nThis confirms the referral system is in a **code and linking stage only** — the rewards/earnings mechanics are not yet modeled in the DB.\n\nFull file path: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/services/backend/src/db.ts`"},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: ab3a9232f9f22f787 (use SendMessage with to: 'ab3a9232f9f22f787' to continue this agent)\n<usage>total_tokens: 45505\ntool_uses: 1\nduration_ms: 13270</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"7e052405-15aa-4b3b-94b0-00f5b3dd543f","uuid":"d683ee16-effb-4e9f-8288-6636913e94a6","timestamp":"2026-03-25T11:34:57.160Z","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Find and read the db.ts file in the backend of the rng-utopia project. I need to see:\n1. The existing referral-related interfaces and methods (there should be ReferralCode, ReferralLink types and methods like insertReferralCode, etc.)\n2. The overall pattern used for DB methods (how they use sql tagged template, how interfaces are defined, pagination patterns)\n3. Any existing claims or earnings-related types\n\nThe file is likely at sources/rng-utopia/services/backend/src/db.ts\n\nRead the entire file. I need to see the full structure, especially the referral section at the end.","agentId":"ab3a9232f9f22f787","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect. I've read the entire db.ts file. Here's a comprehensive summary of what I found:\n\n## Existing Referral System Structure\n\n### Types (Lines 127-143)\n\n**ReferralCode** interface:\n- `id: number` — auto-increment PK\n- `wallet: string` — the code owner\n- `code: string` — the referral code string\n- `created_at: Date`\n- `updated_at: Date`\n\n**ReferralLink** interface:\n- `id: number` — auto-increment PK\n- `referrer_wallet: string` — who referred\n- `referee_wallet: string` — who was referred\n- `created_at: Date`\n\n### DB Methods (Lines 279-305 in Db interface; 657-716 in implementation)\n\n**Codes (insertReferralCode, getReferralCodeByWallet, getReferralCodeByCode, upsertReferralCode)**:\n- Insert throws on duplicate wallet or code\n- Get by wallet or by code string\n- Upsert uses `ON CONFLICT (wallet) DO UPDATE` to replace a wallet's code\n\n**Links (insertReferralLink, getReferralLinkByReferee, getReferralLinksByReferrer)**:\n- Insert throws on duplicate referee\n- Get single link for a referee (1-to-1 lookup)\n- Get all links where wallet is the referrer (1-to-many, ordered newest first)\n\n### Key Patterns I See\n\n1. **SQL tagged template** with postgres library:\n   ```typescript\n   const rows = await sql<Type[]>`SQL QUERY ${param}`;\n   ```\n\n2. **Normalization functions** convert numeric types:\n   - `normalizeRound()`, `normalizeTransaction()`, `normalizeCloseCallRound()` convert BigInt/string fields to numbers\n\n3. **Pagination pattern** (lines 615-650):\n   - Uses `cursor` (string ID) + `limit` (default 20, max 50)\n   - `WHERE ... AND id < ${cursor} ORDER BY id DESC LIMIT ${limit}`\n\n4. **Batch inserts** (lines 599-612):\n   - `.map()` to transform param array to object array\n   - Pass to sql with column names: `sql(values, \"col1\", \"col2\", ...)`\n\n5. **Idempotency** (lines 584-596):\n   - Single inserts use `ON CONFLICT DO NOTHING`\n   - Batch inserts also use `ON CONFLICT DO NOTHING`\n\n6. **Optional field handling**:\n   - COALESCE for updates that preserve existing values: `COALESCE(${newValue ?? null}, existing_column)`\n   - Use `sql.json()` for JSONB fields\n\n---\n\n## What's Missing for a Full Referral System\n\nThe current system only tracks:\n- Who has a referral code\n- Who referred whom (binary relationship)\n\n**No earnings/claims tracking**. There are no:\n- `ReferralEarning` or `ReferralClaim` types\n- Methods like `insertReferralEarning()`, `getReferralEarnings()`, `claimReferralBonus()`\n- Columns tracking: earned amounts, claimed amounts, claim timestamps, or claim status\n\nThis confirms the referral system is in a **code and linking stage only** — the rewards/earnings mechanics are not yet modeled in the DB.\n\nFull file path: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/services/backend/src/db.ts`"}],"totalDurationMs":13270,"totalTokens":45505,"totalToolUseCount":1,"usage":{"input_tokens":5,"cache_creation_input_tokens":14514,"cache_read_input_tokens":30148,"output_tokens":838,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":14514},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}}}
