{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01PnsFyyJnUwtkd2cMCTGyPV","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now I have all the information. Let me compile the detailed findings report.\n\n## Summary Report\n\nI've successfully located and analyzed the three key areas of the RNG Utopia backend. Here's the complete specification:\n\n---\n\n## 1. Referral Schema (`011_referral.sql`)\n\n### Table: `referral_earnings`\n**Purpose**: Tracks per-game earnings for each referee, one row per round (idempotency guard via unique constraint)\n\n**Columns**:\n```\nid                        SERIAL       PRIMARY KEY\nreferrer_wallet           TEXT         NOT NULL\nreferee_wallet            TEXT         NOT NULL\nround_id                  TEXT         NOT NULL         -- matches round PDA\ngame_type                 TEXT         NOT NULL         -- \"coinflip\", \"lord\", etc.\nwager_lamports            BIGINT       NOT NULL         -- amount in each player's entry\nfee_lamports              BIGINT       NOT NULL         -- platform fee collected\nreferrer_earned_lamports  BIGINT       NOT NULL         -- payout to referrer\nreferrer_rate_bps         INTEGER      NOT NULL         -- bps applied (default 1000 = 10%, KOL overrides)\nreferee_rebate_lamports   BIGINT       NOT NULL         -- cashback to referee\nreferee_rebate_rate_bps   INTEGER      NOT NULL         -- bps applied (default 500 = 5%)\ncreated_at                TIMESTAMPTZ  DEFAULT now()\n\nUNIQUE CONSTRAINT: (referee_wallet, round_id)  -- prevents duplicate earnings per round\nINDEXES:\n  - idx_referral_earnings_referrer (referrer_wallet, created_at)\n  - idx_referral_earnings_referee (referee_wallet, created_at)\n  - idx_referral_earnings_round_id (round_id)\n```\n\n### Table: `referral_claims`\n**Purpose**: Tracks async SOL payout requests with settlement status\n\n**Columns**:\n```\nid              UUID         PRIMARY KEY (gen_random_uuid())\nwallet          TEXT         NOT NULL\namount_lamports BIGINT       NOT NULL\nstatus          TEXT         DEFAULT 'pending'\ntx_signature    TEXT                             -- null until completed\nerror           TEXT                             -- null if success\nrequested_at    TIMESTAMPTZ  DEFAULT now()\nprocessed_at    TIMESTAMPTZ                      -- null until completed\n\nCHECK CONSTRAINT: status IN ('pending', 'processing', 'completed', 'failed')\nINDEXES:\n  - idx_referral_claims_wallet (wallet, requested_at)\n  - idx_referral_claims_status (status) WHERE status IN ('pending', 'processing')\n```\n\n### Table: `referral_kol_rates`\n**Purpose**: Custom referrer rates for KOL partners (overrides default 1000 bps)\n\n**Columns**:\n```\nwallet          TEXT         PRIMARY KEY\nrate_bps        INTEGER      NOT NULL         -- e.g., 1500 = 15%\nset_by          TEXT         NOT NULL         -- admin wallet\ncreated_at      TIMESTAMPTZ  DEFAULT now()\nupdated_at      TIMESTAMPTZ  DEFAULT now()\n```\n\n### Table: `referral_codes`\n**Purpose**: One-to-one mapping of wallet → player-chosen referral code\n\n**Columns**:\n```\nid              SERIAL       PRIMARY KEY\nwallet          TEXT         NOT NULL UNIQUE\ncode            TEXT         NOT NULL UNIQUE  -- 3-16 chars [a-z0-9-]\ncreated_at      TIMESTAMPTZ  DEFAULT now()\nupdated_at      TIMESTAMPTZ  DEFAULT now()\n```\n\n### Table: `referral_links`\n**Purpose**: Immutable referrer → referee binding (one referrer per player)\n\n**Columns**:\n```\nid              SERIAL       PRIMARY KEY\nreferrer_wallet TEXT         NOT NULL\nreferee_wallet  TEXT         NOT NULL UNIQUE  -- one referrer per player\ncreated_at      TIMESTAMPTZ  DEFAULT now()\n\nINDEX: idx_referral_links_referrer (referrer_wallet)\n```\n\n---\n\n## 2. Settlement Data Flow (`settle-tx.ts` + `settlement.ts`)\n\n### Settlement Entry Points\nBoth games follow the same pattern:\n\n#### Coinflip: `settleMatch(deps, pda)`\n**Available fields at settlement time**:\n```javascript\n{\n  creator: PublicKey,\n  opponent: PublicKey,\n  creatorSide: number (0 or 1),\n  entryAmount: bigint,                    // single player's wager\n  algorithmVer: number,\n  feeBps: number,                         // from PlatformConfig\n  treasury: PublicKey,\n  \n  // Computed during settlement:\n  pool: bigint = entryAmount * 2n,\n  feeAmount: number = (pool * feeBps) / 10_000n,\n  payoutAmount: number = pool - feeAmount,\n  resultHash: Buffer (SHA256),\n  resultSide: number (0 or 1),\n  winner: PublicKey\n}\n```\n\n#### Lord of RNGs: `settleLordRound(deps, pda)`\n**Available fields at settlement time**:\n```javascript\n{\n  entries: Array<{\n    player: PublicKey,\n    amountLamports: bigint\n  }>,\n  totalAmountLamports: bigint,\n  algorithmVer: number,\n  feeBps: number,\n  treasury: PublicKey,\n  \n  // Computed during settlement:\n  feeAmount: number = (totalAmountLamports * feeBps) / 10_000n,\n  payoutAmount: number = totalAmountLamports - feeAmount,\n  rentRefund: number,\n  winningOffset: bigint,\n  winnerEntryIndex: number,\n  winner: PublicKey\n}\n```\n\n### Database Updates at Settlement\nBoth games call:\n1. `db.updateRoundPhase(pda, \"settled\", { settle_tx, result_hash, result_side, winner, settle_attempts })`\n2. `db.updateRoundEntries(pda, entries)` — stores serialized array to `rounds.entries` JSONB column\n3. `db.insertOperatorEvent(pda, \"settle_confirmed\", {...})` — logs event details including fee/payout breakdown\n4. `db.insertTransaction({ wallet, game, matchId, txType: \"payout\", amountLamports, txSig })` — payout transaction record\n\n### Key Fields Available for Referral Processing\n```javascript\n{\n  round_id: string (from rounds.match_id),\n  game_type: string (\"coinflip\" or \"lord\"),\n  wager_lamports: bigint (entry_amount for coinflip, or individual entry amount for lord),\n  fee_lamports: number (feeAmount from settlement calc),\n  payoutAmount: number (for winner),\n  referrer_wallet: string,\n  referee_wallet: string,\n  winner: string\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n## 3. Event Queue System\n\n### Event Types (defined in `event-types.ts`)\n```javascript\nEventTypes = {\n  REFERRAL_CODE_APPLIED: \"referral.code_applied\",\n  REFERRAL_GAME_SETTLED: \"referral.game_settled\",\n  REFERRAL_CLAIM_REQUESTED: \"referral.claim_requested\",\n}\n\ntype EventType = (typeof EventTypes)[keyof typeof EventTypes]\n```\n\n### Event Queue Table Schema (`event_queue`)\n```sql\nid              BIGSERIAL    PRIMARY KEY\nevent_type      TEXT         NOT NULL         -- matches EventTypes enum\npayload         JSONB        NOT NULL         -- handler receives as Record<string, unknown>\nstatus          TEXT         DEFAULT 'pending'\nattempts        INTEGER      DEFAULT 0\nmax_attempts    INTEGER      DEFAULT 3\nscheduled_at    TIMESTAMPTZ  DEFAULT now()\nstarted_at      TIMESTAMPTZ                  -- null until processing starts\ncompleted_at    TIMESTAMPTZ                  -- null until completion\nerror           TEXT                         -- null if success\ncreated_at      TIMESTAMPTZ  DEFAULT now()\n\nCHECK CONSTRAINT: status IN ('pending', 'processing', 'completed', 'failed', 'dead')\nINDEXES:\n  - idx_event_queue_poll (scheduled_at) WHERE status = 'pending'\n  - idx_event_queue_status (status, created_at)\n```\n\n### Event Emission API (`emitEvent`)\n```typescript\nasync function emitEvent(\n  tx: SqlOrTransaction,           // PostgreSQL transaction handle\n  eventType: EventType,           // \"referral.game_settled\", etc.\n  payload: Record<string, unknown>,\n  options?: {\n    maxAttempts?: number;         // default: 3\n    scheduledAt?: Date;           // default: now()\n  }\n): Promise<{ eventId: bigint }>\n```\n\n**Atomicity**: Events are committed within the same database transaction as the triggering operation (e.g., settlement update).\n\n### Handler Registration API\n```typescript\n// Register handler for an event type\nregisterHandler(eventType: EventType, handler: EventHandler)\n\n// Retrieve handler\ngetHandler(eventType: string): EventHandler | undefined\n\n// Clear all handlers (test isolation)\nclearHandlers()\n\n// Handler signature\ntype EventHandler = (payload: Record<string, unknown>) => Promise<void>\n```\n\n### Worker Pattern\n- **Polling**: Worker queries `event_queue` WHERE `status = 'pending'` with `SKIP LOCKED`\n- **Concurrency**: Safe to run multiple workers; `SKIP LOCKED` prevents contention\n- **Idempotency**: Handlers must be idempotent (reprocessing with same payload = safe no-op)\n- **Retry**: Failed events increment `attempts`; moves to `dead` after `max_attempts` exceeded\n\n---\n\n## 4. Settlement → Referral Flow Overview\n\nWhen a game settles (Coinflip or Lord):\n\n1. **Settlement submission** in `settle-tx.ts`:\n   - Computes result hash, winner, fee amount\n   - Updates `rounds.phase` → \"settled\"\n   - Inserts payout `transaction` record\n\n2. **Settlement confirmation**:\n   - Updates `rounds` with `result_hash`, `result_side`, `winner`, `settle_attempts`\n   - Inserts `operator_event` (logs settlement details including fee breakdown)\n   - Should emit `EventTypes.REFERRAL_GAME_SETTLED` event with payload including:\n     ```javascript\n     {\n       round_id: string,\n       game_type: string,\n       wager_lamports: bigint,\n       fee_lamports: bigint,\n       winner: string,\n       // Additional context for handler\n     }\n     ```\n\n3. **Event queue processing**:\n   - Event handler (`REFERRAL_GAME_SETTLED`) queries referral links\n   - Calculates referrer/referee shares based on `referral_kol_rates` or defaults\n   - Inserts `referral_earnings` row (protected by unique constraint on `referee_wallet, round_id`)\n   - Accumulates earnings for later claim\n\n---\n\n## File Paths (Absolute)\n- **Referral schema**: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/services/backend/migrations/011_referral.sql`\n- **Settlement logic**: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/services/backend/src/worker/settle-tx.t